(22891, 23535, 2, 1, '', '&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;Scourge of Hebra Sky&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This three-headed monster with lightning, fire, and ice attributes first appeared after the Upheaval. Fighting it alone is inadvisable, as it can launch coordinated elemental attacks with staggering brutality. You must be well-prepared to survive an entanglement with this beast.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, 1),
(22892, 23536, 2, 1, '', '&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;Scourge of Necluda Sky&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This three-headed monster with lightning, fire, and ice attributes first appeared after the Upheaval. Fighting it alone is inadvisable, as it can launch coordinated elemental attacks with staggering brutality. You must be well-prepared to survive an entanglement with this beast.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, 1),
(22893, 23537, 2, 1, '', '&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;Scourge of Gerudo Sky&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This three-headed monster with lightning, fire, and ice attributes first appeared after the Upheaval. Fighting it alone is inadvisable, as it can launch coordinated elemental attacks with staggering brutality. You must be well-prepared to survive an entanglement with this beast.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, 1),
(22894, 23538, 2, 1, '', '&lt;p&gt;Equipment: Magic Rod&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;These spell-casting monsters can be found all over Hyrule. They hurl multiple balls of electricity, summon monsters surging with electricity, and have been known to cause thunderstorms in the area. They are more resilient and dangerous than Electric Wizzrobes.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, 1),
(22895, 23539, 2, 1, '', '&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: center&quot;&gt;Guardian of the Rising Island Chain&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A construct composed of interconnected blocks, made by the Zonai with advanced techniques and magic.  It can rearrange the blocks to change its shape at will. To provide sufficient energy to power its gigantic form, this construct contains a massive store of Zonai charge.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, 1),
